EXPRESSIONS
Evaluate to a value.
Can always be part of a statement.
Can appear in statement positions, function arguments, and right-hand sides of assignment operators.
3 + 5
map(lambda x: x*x, range(10))
[a.x for a in some_iterable]
yield 7
a = 7

STATEMENTS
Perform an action.
Cannot return a value and cannot be used in an expression.
Often contain expressions as parts of their structure (like the expression in an if statements condition).
print(42);
if (x): do_y();
return
a = 7; (with semicolon)
